	<h1>
		Key Risks</h1>
	<p>
		&bull; No guarantees can be given in respect of either income or capital gains;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; Past performance is not a reliable indicator of future results;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; The value of any investment in the Fund can go down as well as up. Investors may not get back the full amount invested;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; The values ascribed to properties for valuation purposes will generally be a matter of the valuer&#39;s opinion, may fluctuate up or down and may not be realisable;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; Comparative to other asset classes, such as equities and bonds, property is an illiquid asset class. Under certain markets conditions investors seeking to redeem their holdings may experience significant restrictions or delays;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; There is no open market for the units in the Fund or the Exempt Trust and redemptions can only be made on certain dates and subject to the terms of the relevant Trust Deed and this Information Memorandum; &bull; Investment is only open to informed and experienced investors;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; The Fund may utilise borrowings, which may be used to acquire investments or for meeting redemption requests, and interest rate movements may, therefore, affect the performance of the Fund. Debt creates an opportunity for increased total return. However, it will also increase the exposure of the Fund to capital loss and interest costs;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; Subscriptions into the Fund and the Exempt Trust are not covered by the UK Financial Services Compensation Scheme or by any other compensation scheme;</p>
	<p>
		&bull; All information presented is based on the Trust Manager&rsquo;s understanding of current law and practice. Changes may adversely affect freehold ground rent values, income levels, growth prospects and tax liabilities. None of the FIT Trustee, the Trust Manager, the Trustee of FET nor the Property Manager nor any of their advisers can accept any responsibility if there is any change in the law, in HM Revenue &amp; Customs&rsquo; practice or in the tax treatment of the Fund, the Exempt Trust or of Investors.</p>
	<p>
		The foregoing list of risk factors is not comprehensive and the attention of prospective investors is drawn to the risk factors contained within the Information Memorandum.</p>
</section>
